Type: Package
Package: splitTools
Title: Tools for Data Splitting
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2020-01-03
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Michael",
           family = "Mayer",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "mayermichael79@gmail.com")
Maintainer: Michael Mayer <mayermichael79@gmail.com>
Description: Fast, light-weight tool box for data splitting.
    Data sets can be split into disjoint groups (e.g.
    training/validation/test) or into (repeated) k-folds for subsequent
    cross-validation. Besides basic splits, the package supports
    stratified as well as grouped splits.
License: GPL(>= 2)
URL: https://github.com/mayer79/splitTools
BugReports: https://github.com/mayer79/splitTools/issues
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    stats
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
